org.apache.hadoop.hive.ql.txn.compactor

Class Initiator

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Thread
      • org.apache.hadoop.hive.ql.txn.compactor.Initiator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Runnable, org.apache.hadoop.conf.Configurable, MetaStoreThread

    public class Initiator
extends Thread
    A class to initiate compactions. This will run in a separate thread. It's critical that there exactly 1 of these in a given warehouse.

      • init

        public void init(AtomicBoolean stop,
                 AtomicBoolean looped)
          throws MetaException
        Description copied from interface: MetaStoreThread
        Initialize the thread. This must not be called until after Configurable.setConf(Configuration) and MetaStoreThread.setThreadId(int) have been called.
        Specified by:
        init in interface MetaStoreThread
        Parameters:
        stop - a flag to watch for when to stop. If this value is set to true, the thread will terminate the next time through its main loop.
        looped - a flag that is set to true everytime a thread goes through it's main loop. This is purely for testing so that tests can assure themselves that the thread has run through it's loop once. The test can set this value to false. The thread should then assure that the loop has been gone completely through at least once.
        Throws:
        MetaException

      • findUserToRunAs

        protected String findUserToRunAs(String location,
                                 Table t)
                          throws IOException,
                                 InterruptedException
        Determine which user to run an operation as, based on the owner of the directory to be compacted. It is asserted that either the user running the hive metastore or the table owner must be able to stat the directory and determine the owner.
        Parameters:
        location - directory that will be read or written to.
        t - metastore table object
        Returns:
        username of the owner of the location.
        Throws:
        IOException - if neither the hive metastore user nor the table owner can stat the location.
        InterruptedException

        Parameters:

        Returns:
        true if the job should run as the current user, false if a doAs is needed.
